Search API question.  We are using <http://tray.io|tray.io> to integrate our product with HubSpot (and other integrations) and there is a discrepancy between how the HubSpot docs say the search API works and what I can make work via tray.  Basically within the “filterGroups” payload, the api docs says to include a list of filters.  But when I use the Tray equivalent, in order to make it work I need to send
```"filter_groups": [
		[
			{
				"check_property_value": {
					"property_name": "HubSpot_owner_id",
					"operator": "EQ",
					"value": "92983899"
				}
			}
		]
	]```
Does anyone know if there is documentation for the “check_property_value” and other possible entries within filterGroups?  Is this perhaps an older API version and I need to switch to using raw HTTP requests to match the document? If anyone has encountered this or has a pointer to docs, I would really appreciate it.
